title: Week 15 NFL Recap: Jets win their 1st game, Chiefs beat Saints in possible Super Bowl preview, Patriots will miss the playoffs (Football 12/21)
description:
Sign up for the CBS Sports Holiday Wishes Sweepstakes: https://www.cbssports.com/general/news/holiday-giveaway/
--------------------------
As they do every Sunday, the Pick Six Superfriends link up late at night to recap all the action in the NFL. Will Brinson, Ryan Wilson and John Breech cover everything you need to know from Week 15 including the Jets miraculously winning a football game and in the process, knocking themselves out of the #1 draft spot. The guys also focus on the Chiefs win over the Saints, the Patriots officially missing the playoffs for the first time in 12 seasons and playoff races in both the AFC and NFC.
Chiefs-Saints (5:20)
Jets-Rams (17:15)
Dolphins-Patriots (28:15)
Ravens-Jaguars (41:30)
Browns-Giants (47:45)
Cardinals-Eagles (59:45)
Bears-Vikings (1:10:00)
Seahawks-Vikings (1:18:45)
Cowboys-49ers (1:25:45)
Bucs-Falcons (1:27:45)
Colts-Texans (1:33:00)
Titans-Lions (1:33:00)
Winners/Losers
